      "code": "{\"query\": \"WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR Windows 10 i5-7300HQ HP laptop root cause analysis 2025 2026\", \"numResults\": 5}",
      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_b927e3a94f134b04850b3ebba98e3de7\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://community.intel.com/t5/Mobile-and-Desktop-Processors/WHEA-uncorrectable-errors/td-p/1564951\",\n      \"title\": \"\\n\\tWHEA uncorrectable errors... - Intel Community\\n\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2025-11-20\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"It never happens when I'm working on something, but weirdly, when I do simple stuff, like clicking \\\"turn off\\\" button, or close the internet browser, blue screen appears.\\n\\nI already have done most of the test, like shkdsk, HP Diagnostic program, also memory test, Intel Processor Diagnostic Tool. All of them said I have no problem. Also test from BIOS stuff, like testing on boot screen. No problems were detected at all.\\n\\nAll my drivers are new as well.\\n\\nSome posts say that undervolting can be a problem, also I didn't do that as well.\\n\\nAlso I have re-installed the window as well but still same.\\n\\nhere I attach the log. Thank you!\\n\\n```\\nWHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR (124)\\nA fatal hardware error has occurred. Parameter 1 identifies the type of error\\nsource that reported the error. Parameter 2 holds the address of the\\nnt!_WHEA_ERROR_RECORD structure that describes the error condition. Try !errrec Address of the nt!_WHEA_ERROR_RECORD structure to get more details.\\nArguments:\\n\\n...\\n\\nintel.com/rss/message?board.id=processors&message.id=68961)\\n* \\n* Permalink\\n* Print\\n* \\n* Report Inappropriate Content\\n\\nHi, AndyWoo.\\n\\nThank you for waiting. After looking carefully into the issue, this might be caused by many different reasons.\\n\\nTo fix it, try the following tips in order, as the first or any following step might resolve your issue.\\n\\n* **Reboot** the system and **enter** BIOS settings, **set** the BIOS to its default settings, and **reboot** the system.\\n* **Remove** any hardware or drivers that were installed recently to see if they are causing the issue.\\n* If unable to start with normal mode, **start** Windows in safe mode.\\n  \\n    + **Check** if there are any driver errors in the device manager and **update the device driver** for the devices that are showing errors.\\n* **Get the latest updates** with Windows Update. **Go** **to** _Settings_ → _Update & security_ → _Windows Update_ , and then **select** _Check for updates_ . When done, **reboot** your system.\\n* **Check** if there are any hardware issues.\\n  \\n    + **Try** to boot with minimal hardware settings (for example, one DRAM, less hardware components on your system).\\n    + **Test** DRAM: Try the Windows 10 app called _Windows Memory Diagnostic_ to check for memory issues.\\n    + **Test** the processor, using the Intel® Processor Diagnostic Tool which can be [downloaded here](https://downloadcenter.intel.com/download/19792/Intel-Processor-Diagnostic-Tool) . For more information about the tool, see [The Intel® Processor Diagnostic Tool](https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/support/articles/000005567/processors.html) .\\n    + **Check** the power supply.\\n    + **Try** to test other hardware in the system. (For example, if another working hard drive is available, then use it instead.)\\n\\nYou may also visit this Microsoft link: ( <https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-7c49d78a-2792-96cf-2268-abbe9d9eb29f> ) for more details.\\n\\nBest regards,\\n\\nVon M.\\nIntel Customer Support Technician\\n\\n0 Kudos\\n\\n[](https://community.intel.com/t5/forums/v5/forumtopicpage.kudosbuttonv2.kudoentity:kudoentity/kudosable-gid/1566933?t:ac=board-id/processors/thread-id/68740&t:cp=kudos/contributions/tapletcontributionspage \\\"Click here to give kudos to this post.\\\")\\n\\nCopy link\\n\\nReply\\n\\nAndyWoo\\n\\n[AndyWoo](https://community.intel.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/335491)\\n\\nNovice\\n\\n‎01-29-2024 08:20 AM\\n\\n129,533 Views\\n\\n* Mark as New\\n* Bookmark\\n* Subscribe\\n* Mute\\n* \\n* [Subscribe to RSS Feed](https://community.intel.com/rss/message?board.id=processors&message.id=68976)\\n* \\n* Permalink\\n* Print\\n* \\n* Report Inappropriate Content\\n\\nThank you for your reply. I have tried most of methods that you kindly mentioned.\\n\\n* BIOS setting - I tried.\\n* Remove hard\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/Notebook-Boot-and-Lockup/quot-WHEA-UNCORRECTABLE-ERROR-quot-on-HP-Envy/td-p/5023542\",\n      \"title\": \"Solved: \\\"WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR\\\" on HP Envy\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Solved: \\\"WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR\\\" on HP Envy\\nSolved: A bit ago I was using my HP Envy laptop as normal, just watching a video on Youtube when it crashed and I got a blue screen with the error\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XSuitnjGWv8\",\n      \"title\": \"FIX Blue Screen WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"How to Fix WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR in Windows 10. AOMEI•148K views &middot; 9:44 &middot; Go to channel Ask Your Computer Guy &middot; Discover the Secret to\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://techlasi.com/pc/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-02-12\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\\n\\nBy [MK Usmaan](https://techlasi.com/author/mkusman22/ \\\"View all posts by MK Usmaan\\\") / February 12, 2026\\n\\nAre you facing the dreaded blue screen with a WHEA uncorrectable error message? You’re not alone. This frustrating hardware related error has troubled computer users for years, but with advances in diagnostic technology in 2026, we now have better solutions than ever before. This comprehensive guide will walk you through everything you need to know about WHEA errors, from understanding what they are to implementing the most effective fixes using the latest tools and techniques.\\n\\nWHEA Uncorrectable Error\\n\\n## **What is a WHEA Uncorrectable Error?**\\n\\nA WHEA (Windows Hardware Error Architecture) uncorrectable error occurs when Windows detects a serious hardware problem that it cannot recover from automatically.\\nUnlike correctable hardware errors that Windows can resolve on the fly, uncorrectable errors force your system to shut down to prevent potential damage to your hardware or data corruption.\\n\\n### **Windows Hardware Error Architecture**\\n\\nWindows Hardware Error Architecture is a platform level error handling mechanism introduced in [Windows Vista](https://techlasi.com/savvy/windows-vs-linux-vs-macos/) that provides a standardized way for the operating system to handle hardware errors. WHEA improves upon the older Machine Check Architecture by offering enhanced error reporting and more detailed diagnostic information.\\n\\nTable of Contents\\n\\n* What is a WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n  \\n    + Windows Hardware Error Architecture\\n    + Common Error Codes Associated with WHEA Errors\\n* Primary Causes of WHEA Uncorrectable Errors\\n  \\n    + Hardware Component Failures\\n    + Overclocking Issues\\n    + Driver and Firmware Problems\\n* Symptoms and Identification of WHEA Uncorrectable Errors\\n+ Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) Appearances\\n    + Event Viewer Diagnostics\\n* Step-by-Step Troubleshooting Guide\\n  \\n    + Immediate Actions to Take\\n    + Advanced Diagnostic Procedures\\n    + Hardware Component Verification\\n* Prevention Strategies for WHEA Errors\\n  \\n    + Proper System Maintenance\\n    + Cooling Solutions and Temperature Management\\n    + Safe Overclocking Practices\\n* Recent Developments in WHEA Error Management\\n  \\n    + Advanced Diagnostic Tools\\n    + AI Assisted Troubleshooting\\n* Conclusion\\n* FAQs\\n  \\n    + Can software cause WHEA uncorrectable errors?\\n    + How can I tell which hardware component is causing my WHEA error?\\n    + Are WHEA errors covered under warranty?\\n    + Can updating BIOS fix WHEA uncorrectable errors?\\n    + Why do WHEA errors sometimes occur only during specific activities like gaming?\\n\\n...\\n\\n### **How can I tell which hardware component is causing my WHEA error?**\\n\\nThe most reliable method is checking the Event Viewer logs for WHEA Logger entries. These logs typically specify which component reported the error (CPU, memory controller, etc.). The 2026 Windows Diagnostic Suite also includes a “Hardware Error Source Identifier” that can pinpoint the failing component with approximately 92% accuracy based on error pattern analysis.\\n\\n### **Are WHEA errors covered under warranty?**\\n\\nYes, persistent WHEA errors caused by hardware defects are typically covered under manufacturer warranties. Before making a warranty claim, document all troubleshooting steps you’ve taken and collect system logs that demonstrate the hardware failure. Many manufacturers now accept diagnostic files generated by their official utilities as evidence for RMA (Return Merchandise Authorization) processes.\\n\\n### **Can updating BIOS fix WHEA uncorrectable errors?**\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://community.spiceworks.com/t/whea-uncorrectable-error-blue-screen-help/538876\",\n      \"title\": \"whea uncorrectable error blue screen HELP! - Software & Applications - Spiceworks Community\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2016-11-10\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"( I see this a lot in my office on new HP Laptops running Windows 7, since the hardware specific drivers do not exist in 7.)\\n\\n[jodi-raegilbert](https://community.spiceworks.com/u/jodi-raegilbert) (J\\\\_Rae) November 9, 2016, 3:33am 11\\n\\nI had this happen on a brand new Dell PC - twice in a matter of months. The first time, they sent a tech out three days in a row after I ran diagnostics, took out the graphics card, and reseated the memory. They had the techs replace memory twice, then the processor. The processor replacement finally fixed it. The second time, I reseated the memory and it’s been fine ever since. That was just a few weeks ago. Luckily the data on the SSD was safe. Fingers crossed that that’s the end of that, but if happens again I’d suspect the motherboard.  \\nHope this helps. Good luck.\\n\\n[as007](https://community.spiceworks.com/u/as007) (Stiegelis) November 9, 2016, 9:04am 12\\n\\ncheck PSU connection/ try different PSU. does booting in safe mode do the trick?\\nof so there might be a driver conflict\\n\\n[joshdrury](https://community.spiceworks.com/u/joshdrury) (SilentEch0) November 10, 2016, 1:34pm 13\\n\\nI have started warranty returns for the motherboard and processor. The computer will boot into safe mode for about 5 minutes. It blue screened about half way through a sfc /scannow command. I just tried another PSU and same results. Would there be a driver issue if I am reinstalling Windows completely every time. I also pulled the graphics card from the motherboard as well.\\n\\n[CrashFF](https://community.spiceworks.com/u/CrashFF) (CrashFF) November 10, 2016, 7:00pm 14\\n\\nIt is possible to be a driver issue, even with a re-install, specifically if the chipset or CPU supports functions that the driver does not. this is often the case with new Skylake based systems and Windows 7, where Windows 7 is an old enough codebase that it does not have the ability to natively interact with newer hardware functions like xhci USB control.\\n\\n### Related topics\\n|Topic |Replies |Views |Activity |\\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n|[Lenovo Q180, Windows 10 BSOD ntoskrnl.exe+142770](https://community.spiceworks.com/t/lenovo-q180-windows-10-bsod-ntoskrnl-exe-142770/472337)\\n\\nSoftware & Applications\\n\\n[discussion](https://community.spiceworks.com/tag/discussion/2) , [general-windows](https://community.spiceworks.com/tag/general-windows/35) , [windows-10](https://community.spiceworks.com/tag/windows-10/586) |3 |55 |February 12, 2016 |\\n|[HP Spectre WHEA UNCORRECTABLE](https://community.spiceworks.com/t/hp-spectre-whea-uncorrectable/824766)\\n\\nHardware & Infrastructure\\n\\n[hp-hardware](https://community.spiceworks.com/tag/hp-hardware/60) , [question](https://community.spiceworks.com/tag/question/749) |4 |334 |February 10, 2022 |\\n|[Unexpected shutdown of Server (BSOD) with message “WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR”](https://community.spiceworks.com/t/unexpected-shutdown-of-server-bsod-with-message-whea_uncorrectable_error/808494)\\n\\nSoftware & Applications\\n[general-windows](https://community.spiceworks.com/tag/general-windows/35) , [windows-server](https://community.spiceworks.com/tag/windows-server/224) , [question](https://community.spiceworks.com/tag/question/749) |4 |313 |August 16, 2021 |\\n|[Server 2008 blue screen headaches](https://community.spiceworks.com/t/server-2008-blue-screen-headaches/233071)\\n\\nSoftware & Applications\\n\\n[discussion](https://community.spiceworks.com/tag/discussion/2) , [general-windows](https://community.spiceworks.com/tag/general-windows/35) , [windows-server](https://community.spiceworks.com/tag/windows-server/224) |8 |58 |August 20, 2013 |\\n|[Blue screens of death: Finding the culprit](https://community.spiceworks.com/t/blue-screens-of-death-finding-the-culprit/224152)\\n\\nSoftware & Applications\\n\\n[di\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.salvagedata.com/blog/whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Causes and Fixes\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-03-05\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Call 24/7 : +1 (800) 972-3282 Get Help\\n\\nSalvageData logo SalvageData Logo Call 24/7 : +1 (800) 972-3282\\n\\nServices\\n\\nLocations\\n\\nLearn more\\n\\n[Account](https://case.salvagedata.com/login)\\n\\n1. \\n2. / Blog\\n3. / WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Causes and Fixes\\n\\n# WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Causes and Fixes\\n\\nLaptop & PC iPhone & Mac\\n\\nWritten by\\n\\nHeloise Montini\\n\\nHeloise Montini\\n\\nWritten by\\n\\nHeloise Montini is a content writer whose background in journalism make her an asset when researching and writing tech content. Also, her personal aspirations in creative writing and PC gaming make her articles on data storage and data recovery accessible for a wide audience.\\n\\nEdited by\\n\\nLaura Pompeu\\n\\nLaura Pompeu\\n\\nEdited by\\n\\nWith 10 years of experience in journalism, SEO & digital marketing, Laura Pompeu uses her skills and experience to manage (and sometimes write) content focused on technology and business strategies.\\n\\nMarch 5, 2026\\n\\nWHEA Uncorrectable Error: Causes and Fixes\\n\\n...\\n\\nPress **Windows + S** , type \\\" **Create a restore point** ,\\\" and click \\\" **System Restore** .\\\" Select a restore point dated before the error first appeared.\\n\\nSystem Restore does not affect your personal files, but it will remove applications installed after the selected restore point.\\n\\n### **13\\\\. Reset or reinstall Windows**\\n\\n**A Windows reinstall should be a last software resort,** not an early step. If the drive is failing, reinstalling Windows can make data recovery significantly more difficult by overwriting recoverable sectors.\\n\\n**Back up all data first.** Then go to **Settings > System > Recovery** and select \\\" **Reset this PC** .\\\" You can choose to keep your personal files or perform a clean install.\\n\\n**Warning:** Even the \\\"Keep my files\\\" option removes all installed applications. If you cannot boot into Windows, create a Windows installation USB on a separate computer and boot from it to access repair options.\\n\\n### **14\\\\. Contact a data recovery service**\\nIf the WHEA uncorrectable error persists after completing all previous steps, you are most likely dealing with a physical hardware failure that software cannot fix.\\n\\nSigns that it is time to stop troubleshooting and seek professional help:\\n\\n* The error appears in Safe Mode or during recovery tools\\n* Your drive makes clicking, grinding, or buzzing sounds\\n* CHKDSK reports numerous bad sectors or fails to complete\\n* MemTest86 finds persistent memory errors across multiple passes\\n* The error recurs across multiple Windows installations\\n\\nContinuing to run a system with failing hardware significantly increases the risk of permanent data loss. Before the drive degrades further, understanding the potential [data recovery cost](https://www.salvagedata.com/blog/data-recovery-cost) can help you weigh your options.\\n\\n## **How to fix WHEA uncorrectable error on Windows 11**\\n\\nThe WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR occurs on Windows 11 for the same hardware-level reasons as Windows 10.\\nThe 14-step fix sequence above applies to both operating systems.\\n\\nWindows 11 users should also check two additional items:\\n\\n1. Verify that your hardware meets Windows 11's **TPM 2.0** and **Secure Boot** requirements. Systems running Windows 11 on marginally compatible hardware can experience increased instability.\\n2. Windows 11 receives driver updates on a different cadence than Windows 10, so check Windows Update and your manufacturer's site separately for chipset and storage controller driver updates after any major Windows 11 feature update.\\n\\n## **Protect your data before the next crash**\\n\\nThe WHEA uncorrectable error signals a real hardware problem, not a random glitch. Start with the least invasive fixes. Always back up your files before running repair tools. And stop using the system immediately if yo\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/Notebook-Operating-System-and-Recovery/Blue-screen-error-stop-code-WHEA-UNCORRECTABLE-ERROR/td-p/9115716\",\n      \"title\": \"\\n\\tSolved: Blue screen error stop code : WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR - HP Support Community - 9115716\\n\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2024-07-12\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Join the HP Community Solve‑a‑thon | Help Others & Share Your Solutions | Live on Zoom | 2:30 PM to 2:30 AM IST | Every Wednesday [Click here to know more](https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/Community-Blog/HP-Community-Solve-a-thon-Everyone-s-Welcome/ba-p/9621311)\\n\\n## Create an account on the HP Community to personalize your profile and ask a question\\n\\nYour account also allows you to connect with HP support faster, access a personal dashboard to manage all of your devices in one place, view warranty information, case status and more.\\n\\nSign in / Create an account\\n\\n[Learn more](https://support.hp.com/us-en/help/hp-account?jumpid=in_r11498_us/en/topic/ribbon)\\n\\n / Create an account / [Learn more](https://support.hp.com/us-en/help/hp-account?jumpid=in_r11498_us/en/topic/ribbon)\\n\\nCheck out our **[WINDOWS 11 Support Center](https://support.hp.com/us-en/help/windows-10-support-center?\\n\\n...\\n\\nSince you've already tried updating the BIOS, formatting the C drive, and checking for bad sectors, there are a few other steps you can take to troubleshoot and potentially resolve the issue:\\n\\n**Check for Driver Issues** :\\n\\n* Ensure all your device drivers are up to date, especially for critical components like your GPU, CPU, and chipset.\\n\\n**Run Windows Memory Diagnostic** :\\n\\n* Press Win + R, type mdsched.exe, and press Enter.\\n* Choose \\\"Restart now and check for problems.\\\"\\n\\n**Check Event Viewer Logs** :\\n\\n* Press Win + X and select Event Viewer.\\n* Navigate to Windows Logs > System and look for critical errors around the time of the BSOD.\\n\\n**Stress Test Your Hardware** :\\n\\n* Use tools like Prime95 to stress test your CPU and MemTest86 for RAM.\\n\\n**Update Firmware/Drivers** :\\n\\n* Visit the HP support website and ensure all firmware and drivers for your specific model (HP Pavilion Gaming 15-Ec1000) are up to date.\\n\\n**Disable Overclocking** :\\n* If you have any overclocking settings enabled in the BIOS or through software, disable them and see if the issue persists.\\n\\n**Check for Overheating** :\\n\\n* Use software like HWMonitor to check the temperatures of your CPU and GPU to ensure they are not overheating.\\n\\n**Reseat Hardware Components** :\\n\\n* If comfortable, try reseating your RAM, SSD/HDD, and other removable components to ensure they are properly connected.\\n\\n**Run System File Checker (SFC) and DISM** :\\n\\n* Open Command Prompt as an administrator.\\n* Run sfc /scannow and wait for it to complete.\\n* Then run DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /RestoreHealth.\\n\\n**Check PSU and Battery** :\\n\\n* Ensure that your laptop’s power supply unit (PSU) and battery are functioning correctly and providing stable power.\\n\\n**Windows Update** :\\n\\n* Ensure your Windows operating system is fully updated.\\n\\nIf none of these steps resolve the issue, it might be a deeper hardware fault. I recommend you contact phone support.\\n\\nHope this helps!\\nKeep me posted for further assistance\\n\\nPlease mark this post as “ **Accepted Solution** ” if the issue is resolved and if you feel this reply was helpful click “ **Yes** ”.\\n\\n**Nal\\\\_NR-  \\nHP Community Moderator  \\n**\\n\\nView solution in original post\\n\\nTags (1)\\n\\n* Tags:\\n* HP Pavilion Gaming 15-ec1000 Laptop PC (9EK33AV)\\n\\nView All (1)\\n\\nWas this reply helpful? [Yes](https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/forums/v4/forumtopicpage.externalratingdisplay.ratingenumerationdisplay.link:rating/rating-enum/1/rating-system/medaltesttest/message-uid/9117708?t:ac=board-id/OS/thread-id/662980&t:cp=ratings/contributionpage&ticket=r7TbP0rY_dPL_-1) [No](https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/forums/v4/forumtopicpage.externalratingdisplay.ratingenumerationdisplay.link:rating/rating-enum/0/rating-system/medaltesttest/message-uid/9117708?t:ac=board-id/OS/thread-id/662980&t:cp=ratings/contributionpage&ticket=r7TbP0rY_dPL_-1)\\n\\n3 REPLIES 3\\n\\nNal_NR\\n\\nModerat\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/answers/questions/3864635/windows-10-repeating-bsod-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"Windows 10 repeating BSOD: WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2025-05-26\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"If you are able to get into Windows until you share the minidump file, please go to C:\\\\Windows\\\\Minidump and copy any minidump files you find to your desktop. Afterward, share these files through OneDrive or Google Drive so we can analyze them and identify the specific file that's causing the crash.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.justanswer.com/laptop/di51k-laptop-keeps-getting-whea-uncorrectable-error-keeps.html\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error on Your Laptop | Expert Q&A\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"You didn't respond to my question regarding why the primary hard disk self-test passed if there is an issue with the hard drive. Additionally, when I researched the 0301 error, it mentioned that other factors could be causing this, such as BIOS and other reasons. I'm on Social Security disability and don't have the extra funds to purchase a hard drive if that isn't the actual cause.\\n\\nCustomer\\n\\nI won't provide a rating until the task is completed.\\n\\nLaptop technician: Hriday Dhali\\n\\nSure, how many hard disks are there?\\n\\nCustomer\\n\\nOnly the [1] main HDD\\n\\nLaptop technician: Hriday Dhali\\n\\nThe primary hard drive is corrupted, according to the results.\\n\\nCustomer\\n\\neven when the primary hard disk self-test passed, is the hard drive still corrupted?\\n\\nCustomer\\n\\nWhen I researched the 0301 error, I found that it could be caused by other factors, such as the BIOS and various other reasons.\\nI'm on Social Security disability and don't have the extra funds to purchase a hard drive if that's not the actual cause.\\n\\nRead less\\n\\n0 Likes\\n\\nShare:\\n\\nDisclaimer: The customer and expert messages presented herein may have been altered or modified to enhance readability and safeguard the privacy of individuals. These modifications do not change the intent or substance of the original messages.\\n\\nBack\\n\\nHriday Dhali\\n\\n4,483satisfied customers\\n\\nTech Support Specialist\\n\\nHriday Dhali\\n\\nTech Support Specialist\\n\\n4,483satisfied customers\\n\\nAsk your question here\\n\\n5 Tech Support Specialists are online right now.\\n\\nStart chat\\n\\n1\\n\\nMaximize\\n\\n## Dell XPS 15: Fixing WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR Crashes\\n\\n_XPS 15 often faces overheating and driver conflicts causing system instability and crashes._\\n\\nThe WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR indicates hardware issues like failing CPU, RAM, or overheating. Start by updating BIOS and all device drivers.\\nRun memory diagnostics to check RAM health and monitor CPU temperatures using software tools. Clean internal fans and vents to prevent overheating. If errors persist, test hardware components individually, focusing on the CPU and RAM. Reapplying thermal paste can improve cooling. Regular maintenance and driver updates help prevent this error and system restarts.\\n\\n**Disclaimer:** This information is AI-generated and intended for general guidance only. For advice specific to your situation, please consult a verified expert on JustAnswer before making decisions.\\n\\nHave a question? Ask now\\n\\nWelcome! How can I help with your {0} question?\\n\\nNew!\\n\\nHP laptop keeps restarting\\n\\nHP laptop hardware diagnostics missing\\n\\n#### Related Customer Questions\\n\\nView More\\n\\n#### Getting Started Is Easy\\n\\nAsk for help, 24/7\\n\\nAsk for help, 24/7\\n\\nMembers enjoy round-the-clock access to 12,000+ verified Experts, including doctors, lawyers, tech support, mechanics, vets, home repair pros, more.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://umatechnology.org/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide-for-2026\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Check the drive’s SMART health with the manufacturer’s tool, update SSD firmware, reseat the drive if it is removable, and make sure it has adequate cooling. Back up files immediately if the drive reports media errors, critical warnings, or rapid health decline.\\n\\n### Should I update my BIOS or UEFI to fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n\\nA BIOS/UEFI update can help if the problem is related to CPU microcode, memory compatibility, PCIe stability, or a newer processor installed on an older motherboard. Use the motherboard or laptop manufacturer’s exact model page, avoid beta firmware unless support recommends it, and do not interrupt the update. After updating, load optimized defaults before reapplying settings such as XMP, EXPO, undervolting, or fan curves.\\n\\n### Is it safe to keep using a PC that gets WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n\\nOccasional crashes after a bad driver or unstable tuning may not mean immediate hardware failure, but repeated WHEA errors should not be ignored.\\nContinued use can risk data loss if the cause is storage failure, overheating, or unstable power. Back up your data first, remove overclocks, monitor temperatures, and stop heavy workloads until the system passes stability tests.\\n\\n## Bottom Line\\n\\nThe WHEA Uncorrectable Error is usually a sign that Windows detected a serious hardware or low-level system stability problem, so the safest approach is to troubleshoot methodically: undo recent changes, check temperatures, update BIOS/UEFI and drivers, then test memory, storage, CPU, GPU, and power stability.\\n\\nIf the error continues after clean updates, safe settings, and component diagnostics, treat it as a likely failing part rather than a normal software crash. Back up data, stop overclocking, and consider professional testing or hardware replacement before the issue leads to data loss or an unbootable system.\\n\\n####