      "text": "Now I have all the data I need. Let me compile the comprehensive root cause analysis.\n\nKey findings from all diagnostics:\n\n1. **System**: HP OMEN Laptop 15-ce0xx, i5-7300HQ, 16GB RAM, GTX 1050 + HD 630\n2. **Storage**: C: drive at 99.3% full (3.35GB free of 473.9GB), D: drive at 99.3% full (6.55GB free of 931.4GB)\n3. **GPU**: GTX 1050 at 72°C at idle (P8 state), driver from April 2023 (31.0.15.3179)\n4. **NVIDIA latest driver**: 32.0.15.8183 (March 2026) - very outdated\n5. **BIOS**: F.24 from July 2021 - outdated\n6. **Crashes**: \n   - 07/03/2026: 2 crashes (4:10:28 PM, 9:57:32 AM)\n   - 06/20/2026: 2 crashes\n   - 06/17/2026: 1 crash\n   - 05/15/2026: 1 crash\n   - 05/12/2026: 1 crash\n7. **WER bugcheck codes**: 0x0000012b (TDX error - memory controller), 0x000000be (ATTEMPTED_WRITE_TO_READONLY_MEMORY)\n8. **Dump creation failures**: Minidumps not being written (likely due to low disk space)\n9. **Services failing**: XTU3SERVICE, CWAUpdaterService, DSAUpdateService, DSAService, HpTouchpointAnalyticsService\n10. **TPM errors**: Secure boot variable update failures\n11. **Mixed RAM**: SK Hynix + Samsung modulesNow let me compile the full report.",
