      "type": "answer",
      "text": "---\n\n### Final Verdict & Action Plan\n\n#### Fixability Score: **8.5/10** -- Highly Fixable\nThis is a **software/maintenance problem**, not hardware failure. No components need replacing.\n\n#### Priority Fix List (by impact):\n\n| Priority | Action | Impact | Difficulty |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **1** | **Free disk space on C:** -- you have 3.32 GB free on a 474 GB drive (0.7%). Delete temp files, uninstall unused apps, clear browser caches, move large files to D:. Aim for 15-20% free. | **Fixes the BSOD** | Trivial |\n| **2** | **Update NVIDIA driver** from v531.79 (Apr 2023) to v561+ (2026). Download from nvidia.com/drivers. | **Fixes the BSOD** | Trivial |\n| **3** | **Update BIOS** via HP Support Assistant or HP website for OMEN 15-ce0xx. | **Fixes the BSOD** | Easy |\n| **4** | **Clean laptop vents** with compressed air. GPU idling at 74°C (should be 35-45°C). | **Improves temps** | Easy |\n| **5** | Run monitoring script: `python C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\temp_monitor.py` | **Ongoing visibility** | Trivial |\n\n#### Reliability Assessment:\n- **Your hardware is fine.** SSD and HDD both report Healthy. No disk errors. No memory errors in event logs.\n- **Your BSODs are caused by disk thrashing + outdated GPU driver + possible BIOS microcode issue.**\n- **Can you safely use the PC?** Yes, but back up important files first. Crashes will stop once you free disk space and update drivers.\n- **Can you improve temps?** Yes -- clean vents. Your GPU is 25-30°C hotter than it should be at idle. This is dust/thermal paste, not a failing component.\n\n**Bottom line:** Free ~50 GB on C:, update NVIDIA driver, update BIOS, clean vents. Your BSODs should stop and temps should drop 15-20°C.",
